# Security Personal Assistant (SPA) — MVP Requirements & Build Plan

**Status:** Handoff-ready for a coding agent
**Owner:** (you) — Staff Security/GRC Engineer
**Date:** 2026-06-05
**License target:** MIT (public template) + private fork for org content

---

## 0. One-paragraph summary

Build a **portable, GitHub-distributed, local-first agentic Security Personal Assistant** that ingests notes/transcripts, comms, tickets, and cloud findings, then **drafts** GRC artifacts (Linear tickets, policy PRs, control crosswalks, evidence packs). The agent operates **Draft-by-default, Approve-to-publish**: it can autonomously read and draft, but anything that creates an obligation for a human (assignment) or an authoritative record (publishing, merging, GRC writes) is gated behind explicit human approval. GRC-platform and ticket integrations are **adapter-based and disabled in MVP** (platform-agnostic). The unit of delivery is a **reproducible GitHub repo**: clone -> bootstrap -> run.

---

## 1. Goals & non-goals

### 1.1 MVP goals
- G1. Local-first memory (no cloud memory dependency): episodic + semantic + procedural + audit.
- G2. Repo-first portability: clone + one bootstrap script -> working agent on Linux/WSL/macOS.
- G3. Draft-only write surfaces in MVP: local files, agent-owned git branches, **Draft** PRs, **AI-Proposed unassigned** tickets (as files when no provider configured).
- G4. Human-gated approval queue for all people-impacting / authoritative actions.
- G5. Auditable by design: append-only JSONL audit log of prompts, retrieved context, tool calls, approvals, outputs.
- G6. Governance-as-code: a single autonomy-policy.yaml defines all action-risk gates.
- G7. Shareable: strip private content -> public template repo.

### 1.2 Non-goals (explicitly deferred post-MVP)
- N1. Writing to any GRC platform (Vanta/Drata/Secureframe) — adapter stubbed + disabled.
- N2. Auto-assigning work to other humans (suggestions only).
- N3. Auto-merging PRs, publishing policies, sending external comms.
- N4. Production/cloud mutations (IAM, secrets, config) — blocked.
- N5. Multi-user / multi-tenant operation.

