## 2. Assumptions (stated)
- A1. Single-user, always-on Linux/WSL box; Docker available.
- A2. Default runtime: **Hermes Agent** (MIT, local, MCP-compliant, portable skills). Runtime kept swappable behind config.
- A3. Reasoning model via OpenAI-compatible/Anthropic API; local embedding model (e.g., nomic-embed-text) so memory never leaves the box.
- A4. Local vector DB: **Qdrant** (Docker). Episodic store: **SQLite + FTS5**.
- A5. Canonical "Security Brain" = git-backed Markdown/YAML; Obsidian optional editor on top.
- A6. "Shared credentials" = delegated, scoped tokens injected at runtime via .env / secrets mount, never committed, never written to memory.

