## 5. Action-risk model (governance-as-code)

| Class | Approval | Examples |
|-------|----------|----------|
| A0 read | none (log) | read inbox, brain, tickets/findings (adapters off in MVP) |
| A1 local draft | none (log) | write local markdown, create local branch, create CPO |
| A2 external draft | notify only | Draft PR, AI-Proposed unassigned ticket, provenance comment |
| A3 human workflow | REQUIRED | assign human, raise priority > High, change due date |
| A4 authoritative record | REQUIRED | merge PR, publish policy, GRC write (post-MVP) |
| A5 high risk | BLOCKED | prod IAM, secret rotation, delete evidence/logs, risk acceptance |

Defaults: tickets created unassigned/self + suggested owner in body; PRs created as Draft on `agent/` branches with signed commits; policies written to `proposals/` requiring control mapping.

