## 7. Build plan (milestones, handoff-ready)

### Milestone 0 — Repo skeleton & portability spine (Day 1)
Tasks:
- Create repo, LICENSE (MIT), README stub, .gitignore, .env.example.
- Add docker-compose.yml (Qdrant + volume), Makefile targets, .devcontainer.
- Write bootstrap.sh (idempotent) and scripts/seed_brain.py stub.
Acceptance:
- `./bootstrap.sh` on a clean box brings up Qdrant, installs runtime, runs `make selftest` (passes with empty stubs).

### Milestone 1 — Governance spine (Day 1–2)
Tasks:
- Author agent/autonomy-policy.yaml (the action-risk model above).
- Author agent/charter.md (system prompt: persona, Draft-by-default rules, must read autonomy-policy).
- JSON schemas: memory-object, cpo (change proposal object), audit-event.
- governance/redaction-rules.yaml.
- Approval queue CLI: make proposals / show / approve / reject.
Acceptance:
- A hand-created CPO can be listed, shown, approved, rejected; each transition writes an audit event; schema validation passes in CI.

### Milestone 2 — Local memory (Day 2–3)
Tasks:
- SQLite + FTS5 episodic store (schema + read/write/search).
- Qdrant semantic memory: embed via local model (nomic-embed-text), upsert + query.
- Append-only JSONL audit logger.
- Redaction-at-write enforced on all persistence paths.
- `forget` by id/tag.
Acceptance:
- Ingest a sample file -> embedded + searchable; episodic + audit entries created; secret in a fixture is redacted before persistence.

### Milestone 3 — First skills (draft-only) (Day 3–5)
Tasks:
- Skill scaffold (_template) + scripts/new-skill.sh.
- Implement meeting-synth, ticket-draft, policy-redline, csf-crosswalk (csf+soc2 tags), daily-brief.
- Each skill: skill.md, input/output JSON schema, verifiers/, fixtures/, tests/.
- Verifier suite: schema, control-mapping-present, secrets-scan, self-critique rubric (retry-once-then-escalate).
Acceptance:
- `make ingest FILE=evals/fixtures/meeting_sample.md` produces: ticket proposal file(s), control tags, audit log, and (for policy changes) a redline file + Draft-PR-body file on an `agent/` branch. All verifiers pass on golden fixtures.

### Milestone 4 — Connector abstraction (adapters off) (Day 5–6)
Tasks:
- Define connectors/interfaces (ticket, grc, notes, comms) with capabilities + gated_capabilities.
- Implement `none` providers (write proposals/tickets as files).
- mcp/ configs present; all vendor MCPs shipped `.disabled`.
Acceptance:
- With TICKET_PROVIDER=none and GRC_PROVIDER=none, full draft workflow runs file-only; flipping a provider is a config change, not a code change (verified by interface contract test).

### Milestone 5 — CI, evals, redteam, packaging (Day 6–7)
Tasks:
- GitHub Actions: policy-lint, skill-tests (eval fixtures), secret-scan, redteam (prompt-injection corpus).
- evals/run_evals.py scoring drafts vs golden outputs.
- governance/prompt-injection-tests corpus (poisoned transcript, malicious ticket text).
- PR template (requires control impact + provenance), CODEOWNERS.
- README quickstart + architecture diagram; instructions to fork into private repo.
Acceptance:
- All CI checks green on a PR; redteam corpus runs and flags injection attempts; a second person can clone + bootstrap + run meeting-synth in < 30 min.

### Post-MVP backlog (do NOT build in MVP)
- Linear/Jira provider adapters (GraphQL/REST) behind ticket interface.
- GRC provider adapters (Vanta MCP / Drata API / Secureframe REST) behind grc interface, content-gated publisher skill.
- Notion/Drive/SharePoint one-way publish mirrors on policy merge.
- GitHub App identity for PR automation (replace PAT).
- Self-improving skill loop with CODEOWNER-gated skill PRs + reliability metrics dashboard.

